title: Michigan Democratic Primary Vote by County, Michigan, 1.16.2008
name: Michigan Democratic Primary Vote by County, Michigan, 1.16.2008
description: These maps are based on the Michigan Secretary of State Election Website(1) as of 10 minutes past Midnight, January 16, 2008.  These are uncertified" results. National Democratic party had decided to punish Michigan for moving forward its primary date by stripping them of any delegates for the National convention. As a result while Clinton's name remained on the ballot and won the primaries. However, interestingly many who wanted to support either Obama or Edwards voted "Uncommitted".  Clinton won more than 55% vote (~328150) compared to 40% vote for Mr. "Uncommitted" (~236700) .   Two counties,  namely Monroe and Oscoda, out of 83 do not have vote counts available yet.  both Obama and Edwards withdrew their names
